<Link id="l01134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1134"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1135"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// High 16 bits of a 32-bit microMIPS instruction (where the opcode is)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1136"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// always precede the low 16 bits in the instruction stream (that is, they</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1137"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// are placed at lower addresses in the instruction stream).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1138"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1139"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// microMIPS byte ordering:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1140"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   Big-endian:    0 | 1 | 2 | 3</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1141"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   Little-endian: 1 | 0 | 3 | 2</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1142"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1143"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (IsBigEndian) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01144" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1144"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Encoded as a big-endian 32-bit word in the stream.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01145" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1145"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64mipeepholeopt-cpp/#a96d5dc120196819fbfbc257cba09b2aa">Insn</a> =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1146"><Highlight kind="normal">        (Bytes&#91;3&#93; &lt;&lt; 0) | (Bytes&#91;2&#93; &lt;&lt; 8) | (Bytes&#91;1&#93; &lt;&lt; 16) | (Bytes&#91;0&#93; &lt;&lt; 24);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01147" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1147"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01150" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1150"><Highlight kind="normal">             (Bytes&#91;1&#93; &lt;&lt; 24);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1151"><Highlight kind="normal">    &#125; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01152" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1152"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64mipeepholeopt-cpp/#a96d5dc120196819fbfbc257cba09b2aa">Insn</a> = (Bytes&#91;0&#93; &lt;&lt; 0) | (Bytes&#91;1&#93; &lt;&lt; 8) | (Bytes&#91;2&#93; &lt;&lt; 16) |</Highlight></CodeLine>
